      "content": {
        "title": "Supracondylar and Elbow Fractures — Paediatric — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Supracondylar humerus, lateral condyle, medial epicondyle, and radial neck fractures in children with vascular and nerve risk.",
        "summary": "Gartland classification guides supracondylar management. Brachial artery and AIN injury require monitoring. CRPP is common for displaced fractures."
      },
